fine okay um i've noted that in each volume you seem to have a you know a
unifying concept like for the second volume it would be the idea that that man

26:34.700 --> 26:43.900
had to consider himself as a species right in science fiction the third was that
uh we have to have an open mind about the universe and man's fate for science

26:43.900 --> 26:55.980
fiction to exist uh does the fourth volume have that kind of unifying idea
behind it and what would it be? No, what it deals with and those themes really

26:55.980 --> 27:13.420
kind of happened in the first three volumes and when you run into coincidences
like that you feel like something is going right it really happened when I wrote

27:13.420 --> 27:27.440
the first introduction to, or the introduction to volume one, and I realized as
I wrote this introduction that I was setting down three basic requirements and

27:27.440 --> 27:45.240
that these basic requirements for the existence of science fiction, the
recognition of humanity as a species and so forth, somehow fit in with my

27:45.240 --> 27:54.960
concept of how science fiction had developed. And so from there, I picked it up
for volume two and volume three. But I think in this current one,

27:56.640 --> 28:11.780
the genre already has been established by the time we come to 1950, and that now
the major considerations are not generic so much as how are we going to write

28:11.780 --> 28:21.660
it? How are we going to express the ideas, and what ideas are we going to
express, considering the fact that we already have a genre to deal with?

28:24.460 --> 28:40.200
How are the first three volumes sold? Reasonably well. For this kind of book,
the mentor books at New American Library are intended

28:40.200 --> 28:50.480
to be primarily academic books. They also issue them on the mass market, but
they don't expect a major sale on them. And all three of them, at the present

28:50.480 --> 29:01.960
time, or as of six months ago, all three of them have already sold over 30,000
copies each. And they will keep them in print sometime, expect to sell more, of

29:01.960 --> 29:12.060
course, particularly with the issuance of the fourth volume. but they expect,
